# UI layer doctrine

`@mia/ui` is the platform client. Do **not** fake agent `domain/core/runtime`.
Do **not** name folders `shell/`, `chrome/`, `kit/`, `surfaces/`, or top-level `ui/`.

| Kind of code | Put it in |
| --- | --- |
| `main.tsx`, global CSS | `boot/` |
| App root, home pages, workspace frame, session/brand/layout | `app/` |
| REST + SSE transport | `client/` |
| Zustand + SSE reducers | `state/` |
| Product vertical slices (`WidgetType` tiles + private trees) | `widgets/` |
| Presentation-only shared UI | `components/` |
| Hooks / pure helpers / tokens | `hooks/` · `lib/` · `theme/` |

**Hard rule:** `components/` must not import `state/` or `client/`. If it needs store or HTTP, it belongs in `widgets/` or `app/`.

**Forbidden:** `shell/`, `chrome/`, `kit/`, `surfaces/`, `features/`, `api/` (folder), Nest `application/` / `domain/` / `runtime/` / `transport/`.

**Import direction** (enforced by `npm run lint:arch`):

- `components` → `hooks`, `lib`, `theme`, `enums`, `types` only
- `state` → `client`, `lib`, `enums`, `types` — not widgets/components/app
- Outside the package: wire types from `@mia/shared-types` / `@mia/shared-enums` only

Full contract: `docs/doctrine.md`.
